Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reportUnalignedNets(25.10)                          reportUnalignedNets(25.10)

Name
       reportUnalignedNets  - Reports the names of the nets where the pins are
       not aligned

Syntax
       reportUnalignedNets

       [-help]

       [-alignDistance <distance>]

       [-alignFeedThruPins]

       [-considerMacroPinWithinDistance <distance>]

       [-ignoreLength <length>]

       [-noHighlight]

       [-reportAllWithinChannelWidth <width>]

       [-rptFile <filename>]

       [-statistics]

       [-steinerBox]

       [-verbose]

       [[ -ptnToPtn {aligned unaligned  layerMismatch  samePtn  nonNbr  multi-
       Fanout all unplaced none} ]

       [ -topToPtn {aligned unaligned layerMismatch samePtn nonNbr multiFanout
       all unplaced none} ]]

       [-pin_file <filename >| -exclude_pin_file <filename>]

       Reports  the  names  of the nets where the pins are not aligned. It re-
       ports the nets in the following cases:

              * nets that have two pins on  two  different  partitions  and/or
                clones and are not connected to top level hard-macro or I/O.

              * nets  that have two pins that are connected to the same parti-
                tion.

              * nets that have one pin connected to top  level  hard-macro  or
                I/O and the other pin connected to a partition or a clone.

       Notes:

              * The  nets reported by this command are also highlighted in the
                artwork window.

              * The assignPtnPin command internally calls the reportUnaligned-
                Nets command to generate the summary  report  at  the  command
                line.

              * The reportUnalignedNets command measures the average misalign-
                ment with standard deviation for multi-partition nets.

              * The  reportUnalignedNets command detects and reports pins that
                are placed on non-facing edges.

              * The reportUnalignedNets command  ignores  top  level  standard
                cells by default.

Parameters
       -alignDistance <distance>
              Specifies the distance, in microns, up to which the pins are as-
              sumed to be aligned. With this parameter specified, the reportU-
              nalignedNets  command  assumes  that the pins are aligned within
              the specified distance  even  though  they  are  not  physically
              aligned.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -alignFeedThruPins
              Reports the deviation of partition pins from chain's source-tar-
              get box.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -considerMacroPinWithinDistance <distance>
              Reports  nets  connected to macro-pin which are within specified
              distance from nearest partition boundary.

              Default: 3 microns

              Data_type: float, optional

       -exclude_pin_file <filename>
              Specifies the pin list to be excluded for a partition in a file.
              In the pin file, the pins and nets are specified in the  follow-
              ing format:

              Partition: <PtnName/BlockName> <Pin1> <Pin2> <..> <PinN>

              Partition:< PtnName/BlockName> <Pin1> <Pin2> <..> <PinN>

              Nets:< ><netA ><netB ..netN>

              Note:  While specifying the pin list in the pin_file, it is nec-
              essary to give the "Partition" keyword followed by the  name  of
              the  partition or block. If this is not specified, no operations
              are performed.  You can specify multiple partitions in the  same
              pin_file.  The pin_file does not support buses or wild cards for
              pin names. If a pin specified in the list or a partition is  not
              present in the design, a warning is displayed.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each reportUnalignedNets command parameter. For  a
              detailed  description  of the command and all of its parameters,
              use the man command: man reportUnalignedNets

       -ignoreLength <length>
              Specifies the length, in  microns.  It  ignores  the  nets  from
              checking  unalignment  whose  length  is  greater  the specified
              length value.

              Default: 5000

              These ignored nets will be reported in the ignored  category  in
              the output report file.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -steinerBox
              Report the deviation of partition pins from the connectivity box
              of the partition.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -noHighlight
              Disables the highlight capability.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -rptFile <fileName>
              Specifies an output report file.

              Note: Default name for report file is <designName>_unaligned.rpt

              Data_type: string, optional

       -ptnToPtn {aligned unaligned layerMismatch samePtn nonNbr multiFanout
       all unplaced none}
              Reports  nets  that  have  two  pins on two different partitions
              and/or clones and are not connected to top level  hard-macro  or
              I/O.

              * aligned: Reports nets that have aligned pins.

              * all: Reports all categories of unaligned pins.

              * layerMismatch: Reports nets that have pins at an aligned loca-
                tion but different layers.

              * multiFanout: Reports nets that have multiple fanouts

              * none: Disables reporting of nets.

              * nonNbr:  Reports nets that have two pins on two different par-
                titions that are not adjacent.

              * samePtn: Reports nets that have two pins that are connected to
                the same partition.

              * unaligned: Reports nets that have unaligned pins.

              * unplaced: Reports nets that have unplaced pins.

              Data_type: (enum)+, optional

       -pin_file <filename>
              Specifies the pin list for a partition in a  file.  In  the  pin
              file, the pins and nets are specified in the following format:

              Partition: <PtnName/BlockName> <Pin1> <Pin2> <..> <PinN>

              Partition:< PtnName/BlockName> <Pin1> <Pin2> <..> <PinN>

              Nets:< ><netA ><netB ..netN>

              Note:  While specifying the pin list in the pin_file, it is nec-
              essary to give the "Partition" keyword followed by the  name  of
              the  partition or block. If this is not specified, no operations
              are performed.  You can specify multiple partitions in the  same
              pin_file.  The pin_file does not support buses or wild cards for
              pin names. If a pin specified in the list or a partition is  not
              present in the design, a warning is displayed.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -reportAllWithinChannelWidth <width>
              Reports  all  the  unaligned  nets  within the specified channel
              width even if the -ignoreLength parameter has been specified.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -statistics
              Reports average misalignment with standard deviation  and  layer
              difference  count  for  aligned, layer mismatched, and unaligned
              ptnToPtn 2-pin nets of partitions. It is also used for reporting
              pin QOR.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -topToPtn {aligned unaligned layerMismatch samePtn nonNbr multiFanout
       all unplaced none}
              Reports nets that have one pin connected to top level hard-macro
              or I/O and the other pin connected to a partition or a clone.

              * aligned: Reports nets that have aligned pins.

              * all: Reports all categories of unaligned pins.

              * layerMismatch: Reports nets that have pins at an aligned loca-
                tion but different layers.

              * multiFanout: Reports nets that have multiple fanouts

              * none: Disables reporting of nets.

              * nonNbr: Reports nets that have two pins on two different  par-
                titions that are not adjacent.

              * samePtn: Reports nets that have two pins that are connected to
                the same partition.

              * unaligned: Reports nets that have unaligned pins.

              * unplaced: Reports nets that have unplaced pins.

              Data_type: (enum)+, optional

       -verbose
              Reports  all  categories in log file. By default, this parameter
              is not enabled and only the nets that have  unaligned  pins  are
              reported in the log file.

              Note:  There  will  be  no change in the report file with use of
              verbose parameter.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       The following are some of the attributes specified in the output report
       file to report the names of nets where the pins are not aligned:

              * layer mismatch: Specifies nets that have pins  at  an  aligned
                location but different layers.

              * non-neighbor: Specifies nets that have two pins on two differ-
                ent partitions that are not adjacent.

              * ptnToPtn:  Specifies  nets that have two pins on two different
                partitions and/or clones.

              * topToPtn: Specifies nets that have one pin  connected  to  top
                level  hard-macro or I/O and the other pin connected to a par-
                tition or a clone.

              * unAligned: Specifies nets that have unaligned pins.

Example
       The following command reports all nets which are placed  in  a  channel
       equal to or narrower than 7.5 microns irrespective of the -ignoreLength
       parameter.

       reportUnalignedNets  -ptnToPtn  unaligned -rptFile a -ignoreLength 10.0
       -reportAllWithinChannelWidth 7.5

       The following command creates an a.out report file:

       reportUnalignedNets rptFile a.out -noHighlight -ptnToPtn all  -topToPtn
       all

       A  summary  of the reported unaligned nets displays on the Innovus con-
       sole and in the Innovus log file.

